org.jbiowhcore.utility.fileformats.orthoxml

Class Gene

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.jbiowhcore.utility.fileformats.orthoxml.Gene

  • public class Gene
extends Object
    The gene element represents a single gene, protein or transcript. It is in fact a set of identifiers: one internal identifier that is used to link from geneRef elements in ortholog clusters and gene identifiers, transcript identifiers and protein identifiers to identify the molecule. The proper term for this element would therefore rather be molecule. However, as the general purpose of orthoXML is to represent orthology data for genes the term gene is used instead. Gene, protein and transcipt identifiers are optional but at least one of the three should be given. The source database of the gene is defined through the database element in which the gene element lies and the identifiers should stem from this source.

    Java class for gene complex type.

    The following schema fragment specifies the expected content contained within this class. 

     <complexType name="gene">
   <complexContent>
     <restriction base="{http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema}anyType">
       <attribute name="geneId" type="{http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema}string" />
       <attribute name="id" use="required" type="{http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema}integer" />
       <attribute name="protId" type="{http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema}string" />
       <attribute name="transcriptId" type="{http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema}string" />
     </restriction>
   </complexContent>
 </complexType>
